Using pseudocode, write a program that will play the game, "Three Questions."
Just like its overly-complicated forebear, this game has the player think of an object.
The program asks two yes/no questions about the object, then for the third, makes a guess about what it might be.


declare resposta1, resposta2, resposta3

print "està viu?"

resposta1 = read_input

if resposta1 = "Yes" then
	
  print "és un animal?"
	
	resposta2 = read_input
	
	if resposta2 = "Yes" then
		Print "és un gos?
	Else
		Print "és brocoli?"
	End-if

Else 
	
	Print "és un metall?"
	
	Resposta2 = read_input
	
	If resposta2 = "Yes" then
		Print "és ferro?
	Else
		Print "és paper?"
	End-if
	
Resposta3 = read_input

If resposta3 = "Yes" then
	Print "ordenador guanya!!"
Else
	Print "ordenador perd, ohhhh"
End-if


Per jugar "Play again" es pot fer servir una estructura de bucle
